{"session_id":"svc-1778954644759223392","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-16T18:04:05.626856727Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"opus","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"opus","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-7b88e3a7-20260516T180352-74ae6533","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Do not mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; do not use parallel tool calls for `git add`, `git commit`, or other staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 still allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add`, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-7b88e3a7\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eagent: auto_decompose_epic — wrap runPreClaimDecomposer for genuinely-undecomposed epics\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;Genuinely undecomposed epics (IssueType==epic, totalChildCount==0, no closure-pending state) need automated decomposition into child task beads so ddx work can drain them. Today the only decomposition path is operator-invoked (bead-breakdown skill) or post-TooLarge recovery (cli/internal/agent/recovery_decompose.go). FEAT-010 §Idle-Path Diagnosis and Auto-Remediation now requires the work loop to auto-dispatch decomposition for this specific case (RC-6) with strict preconditions to avoid the v1-plan duplicate-child bug.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;No handler exists that bridges the diagnoser\u0026#39;s genuinely_needs_decomposition reason code to runPreClaimDecomposer (cli/internal/agent/recovery_decompose.go:48). The existing post-TooLarge hook (NewDecomposePostLadderExhaustionHook at recovery_decompose.go:107) gates only on TooLarge failure class, not on idle-scan diagnosis.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;Add cli/internal/agent/auto_decompose_epic.go exporting AutoDecomposeEpic(ctx, store, runner, rcfg, projectRoot, beadID) (DecomposeResult, error). It calls runPreClaimDecomposer (reused unchanged) after asserting every precondition. Preconditions (each must hold; first failing precondition produces a typed error AND increments the per-bead auto_decompose_attempted event count):\u0026#xA;- store.Get(beadID).IssueType == \u0026#34;epic\u0026#34;\u0026#xA;- totalChildCount(beadID) == 0 (use the same index ReadyExecutionBreakdown uses)\u0026#xA;- bead is not currently in the EpicClosureCandidate bucket\u0026#xA;- bead has no open dep_blocked_by or closed_or_missing_parent diagnoses (call the new Diagnose function on the bead; if it returns either, return ErrDepsBlockDecompose)\u0026#xA;- bead carries no label in {manual-hold, no-auto-decompose, container}\u0026#xA;- bead description is non-empty AND contains PROBLEM AND PROPOSED FIX sections AND has at least one acceptance criterion AND has at least one label matching ^(spec|area):\u0026#xA;- per-bead event count of auto_decompose_attempted \u0026lt; 3\u0026#xA;- bead has no active execution cooldown\u0026#xA;- (operator override --no-auto-epic-decompose checked at the caller, not here)\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;On success: parent epic\u0026#39;s execution_eligible is set to false (mirrors recovery_decompose.go behavior), child beads are created via store.Create, the auto_decompose_attempted event is emitted with body {child_ids: [...], cost_usd: N}.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;On failure: SetExecutionCooldown(beadID, now+15m, \u0026#34;auto_decompose_failed\u0026#34;, reason, baseRev), emit auto_decompose_failed event. On the 3rd cumulative attempt failure also emit auto_remediation_exhausted so the diagnoser surfaces it.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Wiring this into the work loop (separate bead).\u0026#xA;- Changing the runPreClaimDecomposer prompt (reused as-is).\u0026#xA;- Surfacing the operator override flag (work-loop bead handles flag plumbing).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PARENT AND DEPS\u0026#xA;Parent: ddx-2a1ece2b. Depends on ddx-79e66725 (diagnose function) and ddx-e9f3adaf (RC-1 lifecycle fix — the closure-bucket check needs the correct classifier).\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. cli/internal/agent/auto_decompose_epic.go exports AutoDecomposeEpic with the signature above.\u0026#xA;2. TestAutoDecomposeEpic_HappyPath: bead is a valid undecomposed epic with proper description+AC+labels; AutoDecomposeEpic dispatches the decomposer (use the existing AgentRunner stub from recovery_decompose tests) and creates child beads.\u0026#xA;3. TestAutoDecomposeEpic_PreconditionGates: one sub-test per precondition (non-epic, has children, in closure-candidate bucket, dep-blocked, manual-hold/no-auto-decompose/container label, missing description sections, missing spec:/area: label, attempt count at cap, active cooldown). Each returns the matching typed error and does NOT dispatch the agent.\u0026#xA;4. TestAutoDecomposeEpic_FailureSetsCooldown: dispatcher returns an error; SetExecutionCooldown is called with status=\u0026#34;auto_decompose_failed\u0026#34; and 15m TTL; auto_decompose_failed event emitted.\u0026#xA;5. TestAutoDecomposeEpic_ThirdFailureEmitsExhausted: after three cumulative failures, an auto_remediation_exhausted event is also emitted.\u0026#xA;6. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... -run TestAutoDecomposeEpic -count=1 green.\u0026#xA;7. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./... green.\u0026#xA;8. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ekind:feat, area:agent, phase:2, spec:FEAT-010, spec:FEAT-004\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-2a1ece2b\" base-rev=\"a05e21e9855107daefe01f424639b61b23fdbaa2\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260516T180352-74ae6533\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-7b88e3a7-20260516T180352-74ae6533/.ddx/executions/20260516T180352-74ae6533/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-7b88e3a7-20260516T180352-74ae6533/.ddx/executions/20260516T180352-74ae6533/embedded/git-bin:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/bun/1.3.11/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/node/22.21.1/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-sub